1. Create your portfolio from claude code create index.html file

2. create new repo in github and upload index.html file.

3. Go to repo setting and click on pages select branch main and save it.

4. Then in Actions pipeline will run.

5. Go to settings --> pages you will see at the top your website will be hosted open the site and check website.

6. If you want to add your domain for the website

7. Go to godaddy website and click on profile --> my products --> click on your domain

8. Go to DNS and click on Add new record is this option is disabled go to nameservers --> change Nameservers to default

9. Add new record choose CNAME, in name e.g= gsk, in value = <Github-profile>.github.io e.g= Gaurav-kangane.github.io and save it.

10. Go to reop settings --> pages --> custom domain --> Add name.yourdomain e.g= gsk.gkangane.shop and save it.

11. Check your domain your website will be deployed on that domain.
